AdditionalInformation:
Invited paper for "Special Issue on Animal Locomotion: The Physics of Flying" (editors: Graham Taylor, graham.taylor@zoo.ox.ac.uk; Michael Triantafyllou, mistetri@mit.edu;  Cam Tropea, ctropea@sla.tu-darmstadt.de). 
The research this describes won the IMechE Western Aerospace Centre prize, April 2011 (Phillips, http://nearyou.imeche.org/near-you/UK/Western/Western-Aerospace-Centre/prize-history); 
Data presented informed the test cases subsequently adopted by the NATO working group AVT202 investigating fundamentals of flapping-wing aerodynamics (contact michael.ol@us.af.mil).

As a result of the research into formulation of complex colloidal systems described in this seminal paper and further in subsequent papers, PFL collaborated with Dr Manel Torres (SME Fabrican Ltd) to develop a complex fluid which, when sprayed, forms a fabric. This work culminated in a fashion show at Imperial College in September 2010:http://www3.imperial.ac.uk/newsandeventspggrp/imperialcollege/newssummary/news_21-9-2010-13-23-53,  http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-11339057 .
Numerous invited keynote and plenary lectures have followed, including;
UK Polymer Colloids forum, Hull September (2011) http://www2.hull.ac.uk/science/chemistry/news-and-events/news/uk-polymer-colloids-forum.aspx;
Academy of Pharmaceutical Scientists PharmSci Nottingham September (2012), http://www.ukpharmsci.org/2012resourcepack/Programme/Default.asp;
Formula VII meeting in Mulhouse July (2013) http://www.formulaviimulhouse.uha.fr/fichiers_telecharger/ploneexfile.2012-09-27.1400427787/preview_popup, 
Polymers at Interfaces conference, Bristol, June (2013). http://www.rsc.org/ConferencesAndEvents/conference/alldetails.cfm?evid=111522
